HEADWORD: Fireback
<hw>Fire"back`</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧r"b⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species of pheasants of the genus
<gen>Euplocamus</gen>, having the lower back a bright, fiery red. They
inhabit Southern Asia and the East Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

